# 📁 Component standards (React + SCSS modules)

## Purpose

This document defines the **mandatory standards for all UI components** in this repository.

The goal is to ensure:

* Consistency across the codebase
* Maintainable and scalable structure
* Strong separation of concerns
* Accessibility and performance best practices

***

## 🧱 Core principles

All components must follow these principles:

* ✅ **Encapsulated** — self-contained folder per component
* ✅ **Reusable** — no page-specific logic inside components
* ✅ **Scoped styling** — no global CSS leakage
* ✅ **Accessible by default**
* ✅ **Responsive-first design**
* ✅ **Simple over complex**

***

# 📂 Required folder structure

Every component **must live in its own folder**:

```
/components/ComponentName
  ├── ComponentName.tsx
  ├── ComponentName.module.scss
  ├── ComponentName.types.ts      (optional)
  ├── ComponentName.test.tsx      (optional)
  └── index.ts
```

***

## ✅ Example

``` md
/components/Header
  ├── Header.tsx
  ├── Header.module.scss
  └── index.ts
```

***

# 🧩 Component rules

## 1. Naming conventions

* Component name must be **PascalCase**
* Folder name must match component name exactly

✅ Correct:

```
Header/
Button/
MobileMenu/
```

❌ Incorrect:

```
header/
site-header/
btn/
```

***

## 2. Component implementation

* Use **functional components only**
* Use hooks for state and lifecycle
* Keep components small and focused

✅ Example:

```tsx
import styles from "./Header.module.scss";

export default function Header() {
  return <header className={styles.header}>...</header>;
}
```

***

## 3. Export pattern (MANDATORY)

Each component must use an `index.ts`:

```ts
export { default } from "./Header";
```

✅ This enables clean imports:

```ts
import Header from "@/components/Header";
```

***

# 🎨 Styling standards (STRICT)

## 1. SCSS modules only

All components must use:

```
ComponentName.module.scss
```

✅ Example:

```tsx
import styles from "./Header.module.scss";
```

***

## 2. Prohibited styling approaches

The following are **NOT allowed**:

* ❌ Inline styles
* ❌ Global CSS (unless explicitly defined in `/styles`)
* ❌ Tailwind
* ❌ Styled-components / CSS-in-JS

***

## 3. Class naming

Use **simple, readable class names**:

✅ Good:

```scss
.header {}
.container {}
.nav {}
.scrolled {}
```

❌ Avoid:

```scss
.headerContainerWrapper {}
.mainNavigationListItem {}
```

***

## 4. State-based styling

Use modifier classes:

```scss
.header {}
.scrolled {}
.open {}
.active {}
```

```tsx
<header
  className={`${styles.header} ${isScrolled ? styles.scrolled : ""}`}
>
```

***

## 5. Responsive design

All responsiveness must be handled in SCSS:

```scss
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .nav {
    display: none;
  }

  .hamburger {
    display: block;
  }
}
```

***

# 🔄 Component composition

Complex components should be split into **smaller components**.

## ✅ Example: Header

```
/components/Header
/components/Logo
/components/Nav
/components/MobileMenu
/components/HamburgerButton
```

***

## Rules

* Each subcomponent must follow the same folder structure
* No deeply nested JSX — extract components instead

***

# ⚙️ Behaviour & state

## 1. Local state only

* Use `useState` for UI behaviour
* Avoid global state unless necessary

***

## 2. Side effects

* Use `useEffect` responsibly
* Clean up listeners (e.g. scroll, resize)

✅ Example:

```ts
useEffect(() => {
  const onScroll = () => setScrolled(window.scrollY > 50);
  window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll);

  return () => window.removeEventListener("scroll", onScroll);
}, []);
```

***

## 3. Performance

* Avoid unnecessary re-renders
* Use memoisation if needed (`React.memo`)
* Optimise scroll events (throttle if required)

***

# ♿ Accessibility standards (MANDATORY)

All components must meet **WCAG AA baseline**.

## Requirements

* ✅ Use semantic HTML (`header`, `nav`, `button`)
* ✅ Keyboard accessible
* ✅ Visible focus states
* ✅ ARIA attributes where needed

***

## ✅ Example (hamburger button)

```tsx
<button
  aria-label="Toggle navigation"
  aria-expanded={isOpen}
  className={styles.hamburger}
>
```

***

## Additional requirements

* ESC closes overlays/menus
* Focus should not be lost during interactions
* Interactive elements must be ≥44px

***

# 🔗 Routing standards

* Use `react-router-dom`
* Use `<Link>` for internal navigation

✅ Example:

```tsx
import { Link } from "react-router-dom";
```

❌ Do not use:

``` md
/internal-page
```

***

# 🧪 Testing (recommended)

Where applicable:

```
ComponentName.test.tsx
```

* Test rendering
* Test interactions (clicks, state changes)

***

# 🚫 Anti-patterns (DO NOT DO)

* ❌ Multiple components in one folder
* ❌ Inline styles
* ❌ Mixing layout + business logic
* ❌ Overly large components (>300 lines)
* ❌ Hard-coded data inside components
* ❌ Direct DOM manipulation

***

# ✅ Definition of done (components)

A component is considered complete when:

* ✅ Folder structure is correct
* ✅ Uses `.module.scss` only
* ✅ Is responsive
* ✅ Meets accessibility baseline
* ✅ Has no inline styles
* ✅ Uses clean export pattern
* ✅ Behaviour is tested manually

